Load#

from base.utils_model import load_model

tr, metadata = load_model(
    model_name='fixate4_k-32_z-20x[3,6,12]_enc(1x3)-dec(1x2)-pre(1x3)-post(1x3)',
    fit_name='ep160-b600-lr(0.002)_beta(0.15:0x0.5)_lamb(0.0001)_gr(250.0)_(2023_04_22,15:22)',
    checkpoint=-1,
    device='cuda:1',
    strict=False,
)
print(f"'checkpoint': {metadata['checkpoint']}")

'checkpoint': 160

grads = tr.stats['grad']

fig, ax = create_figure(1, 1, (15, 4))
plt.semilogy(grads.keys(), grads.values(), lw=0.5)
plt.axhline(1000, color='r');

thresholds = [
    tr.cfg.grad_clip * i for i in
    [1, 2, 4, 10, 20, 40, 100, 200, 400, 4000]
]
bad = np.array(list(grads.values()))

t = PrettyTable(['Threshold', '#', '%'])
for thres in thresholds:
    tot = (bad > thres).sum()
    perc = tot / metadata['global_step']
    perc = np.round(100 * perc, 3)
    t.add_row([thres, tot, perc])
print(t, '\n')
